==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gonococcus
<hw>Gon`o*coc"cus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <?/ semen, the genitals + NL. & E. <ets>coccus</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A microorganism (Neisseria gonnorrhoeae) of the
genus <gen>Neisseria</gen> (formerly <gen>Micrococcus</gen>), found in
the secretion in gonorrhea, and constituting the cause of this
disease.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

